title: Potala Incense Sticks (20 sticks per pack)
description:
Patola genuine Tibetan incense is purely hand prepared from highly flavored medicinal herbs and
other precious substances. the combination of genuine scented substances makes the Patola incense
richer and superior quality than other incenses. Our incense is totally absent of choking and
camphor smell and is also non-toxic and non-habit forming. Generally, the Tibetan incense is used
for puja offering and purification but is also used as an air freshener, which keeps ones
surrounding, flavored with a good scent. Length Small ~ 6" Large ~ 10"

title: Red Crystal Incense (27 sticks per pack)
description:
This incense has been made in accordance with a 13th century manuscript on incense making. The
incense has a delightfully fresh and 'serene' fragrance which is excellent for Ritual offering. It
is carefully compounded from 23 traditional medical ingredients brought from their native
environments from the high Himalayan Mountain Range in Kulu, Manali, Sikkim, and Tibet. It is made
by refugee lay people in H. E. Ayang Rinpoche's monastery in Bylakuppe, India. There are many cheap
imitations of this popular incense, made with synthetic perfumes and sawdust filler, and we
guarantee that this is fresh, all-natural, and shipped directly from the monastery. As it is
non-toxic and non-habit forming, its daily use is safe. Length ~ 9.5 inches
